Create Conservation Activity

To create a Conservation Activity:

  1. Select the Create button
  2. Select the context you want the project to be created
     

    Note: You can create the Conservation Activity in the context of a cultural object or in the context of another Project or any system object. Creating Conservation Activity in the context of another system objects means that this Conservation Activity will be part of that context and the permissions on that Conservation Activity will depend on this context.

     

  3. Select "Conservation Activity" from the drop-down with types.
     

    Note: To find easily the Conservation Activity in the list with system objects that can be created you can start to type directly in the field. The list with types is filtered as you write in the field.

     

  4. Fill "Conservation Activity" Details section fields

    Note: Only required fields are displayed in create dialog. I f you want to filled in additional properties you could select 'See more' option that should show all properties of the project, which are not explicitly displayed in create dialog.

  5. Press Create
